Several key players dominate the global myelofibrosis market, with companies like Novartis AG, Bristol-Myers Squibb Company, and Incyte Corporation leading the way. These market players focus on research and development to innovate new treatments and therapies for myelofibrosis patients. Other significant players in the market include Gilead Sciences, Inc., Roche Holding AG, Baxalta, Merck & Co., Inc., Eli Lilly and Company, Celgene Corporation, and Pfizer Inc. These companies collaborate with healthcare professionals and research institutions to improve the diagnosis and treatment options available for individuals diagnosed with myelofibrosis.

